title: 5 bring guns to Nestor party; 2 teens wounded
content:
A 17-year-old was shot and a 14-year-old was clubbed on the head with a shotgun at a party early Saturday, San Diego police said.
Five men or teens showed up with guns and got into an argument with the victims at a Bluehaven Court apartment complex off Servando Drive in the Nestor neighborhood.
One of the gunmen used the butt of a shotgun to hit the younger boy in the head, then fired at the older teen. He was wounded in his left wrist, police Officer Robert Heims said.
Police and medics were called about 12:22 a.m. Medics took both injured teens to a hospital.
Heims said the suspects, all wearing red shirts, left in a dark-colored sedan.
